What you need to know:

Delegations from Senegal, Guinea, Zimbabwe and Malawi arrived at the host city to a heroic reception, but their first group fixtures at the 20,000 seater Bafoussam Omnisport stadium in Kouekong were almost without fansIn a release earlier this week, Cameroon minister of Communication and government spokesperson called on everyone to mobilise and fill the stadiums for the rest of the competitionSenegal will remain in Bafoussam where they will play the flames of Malawi while Guinea and Zimbabwe will travel to Yaounde with their tie set for the Ahmadou Ahijo Stadium